@zoechi The problem is when you want to add content to top of list, Imagine a two way infinite scroll in a chat app.

Current behavior is when you add a content to top of a list, ListView will maintain the scroll position and the visible area is pushed down (or up in reverse).

Android RecyclerView handle this nicely, And for IOS i see an option in [RN's ScrollView called maintainVisibleContentPosition](https://github.com/facebook/react-native/blob/master/Libraries/Components/ScrollView/ScrollView.js#L173).

